If you recognized the quote in the title of my last post as being from
'The Muppet Christmas Carol' then bonus points to you!  It's from the
song that Michael Caine (as Scrooge) sings at the end of the film, which
has been humming through my head since Friday night when it was
(un?)wittingly used in a speech at the Supervisor of the Year awards at
my New Zealand university.  My main advisor, Greg Rawlings, won the
Humanities super of the year at the event...YAY!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!  For any
of you who haven't heard me wax poetic about this man before (and his
impact on my academic life), then let me just say he definitely deserved
the honour!  :) 

