Lots of you have written to say that you're keeping little Thomas in
your prayers and thoughts since I sent out the short note about him last
week.  Thank you!  This is an update about his progress.  He remains in
hospital, basically on a roller coaster ride - his grandmother says that
it seems like for every step forward he makes he takes another back
(take heart - at least he continues to take those steps forward!).  This
weekend he had surgery to begin some kind of dialysis, which will be
ongoing for at least a few days, as well as a blood transfusion
yesterday in response to dropping hemogoblin levels.  But despite that,
his nurse aunt who has gone out to support him and his family says he
seems to be a little more alert and even got to visit with his little
brother for a while which helped to cheer him up.  He is fighting hard,
and can still use all the help we can give him!    

