soon...

I just got a full scholarship for my PhD in New
Zealand!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

Those of you who have an inkling of how many of these awards I've
applied for over the last 3 years will know what a big deal it is to
finally have this nailed down...and I feel GREAT!

(it's getting harder and harder to stay seated people!)

No, I'm not leaving Korea.  Yet.  The university will allow me to keep
my job and collect the award.  :)  So for the time being I am continuing
as before - full-time student and full-time professor - FUN!  When that
scenario changes I'll let you know.  In the meantime, the most exciting
thing about all of this is now having something acceptable to put on my
student visa application form for the NZ gov't!!

YIPPEE, YIPPEE, YIPPEE, dancing circles and jumping for joy!!

